DataElement.preferredName: APGAR Test Heart Rate Score java.lang.Integer
DataElement.preferredDefinition: A test devised by Dr. Virginia Apgar to assess the overall health of a newborn upon birth. The test is administered at one and five minutes after birth and allows for the assignation of numerical values between zero and two for specific observations regarding skin color, pulse rate, reflex irritability, muscle tone and breathing._A component of the APGAR score, it is the numerical value assigned to an assessment of the circulatory status of a neonate. 0 = no pulse; 1 = rate less than 100 beats per minute; 2 = rate greater than 100 beats per minute._Generic value domain for a primitive java dataype that is an Integer (32-bit two"s complement).
